nce >= 0.9\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Oxaloacetate\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network treats oxaloacetate (OAA) as a transient prebiotic hub generated by convergent routes centered on (i) hydrothermal CO2 fixation to pyruvate and related C2-C3 feedstocks, (ii) surface glyoxylate chemistry including cyanide-catalyzed tartrate formation and cyanosulfidic/photochemical production of glyoxylate, and (iii) biochemical/prebiotic mild aqueous network chemistry in which pyruvate and glyoxylate produce OAA within Fe2+-promoted and metal-free protometabolic cycles. Because the literature shows that direct bulk aqueous pyruvate carboxylation is unresolved, this network includes that route only as a specifically identified microdroplet-supported, recent, partially unresolved pathway. OAA is then rapidly consumed to malate, fumarate, succinate, and aspartate-consistent trapping products, reflecting its documented instability.\n\nMOLECULES (20 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: CH2O2 (formate/formic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: C2H4O2 (acetate/acetic acid) [intermediate]\n  - mol_005: C3H4O3 (pyruvate/pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: HCN (HCN) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H2O3 (glyoxylate/glyoxylic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C4H6O6 (tartrate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C4H4O5 (oxaloacetate) [target]\n  - mol_010: C4H6O5 (malate/malic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C4H4O4 (fumarate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C4H6O4 (succinate/succinic acid) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C6H8O8 (oxalomalate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C5H6O6 (4-hydroxy-2-ketoglutarate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: H2O2 (hydrogen peroxide) [starting]\n  - mol_016: CH3NO (hydroxylamine) [starting]\n  - mol_017: C4H7NO4 (aspartate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_018: CO (carbon monoxide) [starting]\n  - mol_019: CH4OS (methyl mercaptan) [starting]\n  - mol_020: CH2O (formaldehyde) [intermediate]\n\nREACTIONS (18 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_003 (Greigite-catalyzed hydrothermal CO2 fixation to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005, mol_003, mol_004 (Native iron reduction of CO2 to pyruvate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005, mol_003, mol_004 (Hydrothermal mineral-catalyzed CO2 fixation to pyruvate on greigite/magnetite systems) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_018, mol_019 -> mol_005 (FeS-mediated hydrothermal synthesis of pyruvate from CO with sulfur activation context) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_005: mol_006 -> mol_007 (TiO2- and sulfide-assisted cyanosulfidic/photochemical generation of glyoxylate from HCN-derived feedstocks) [Surface]\n  - rxn_006: mol_007, mol_006 -> mol_008 (Cyanide-catalyzed glyoxylate dimerization to tartrate) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_008 -> mol_009 (Dehydration of tartrate to oxaloacetate) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_005, mol_007 -> mol_009, mol_010, mol_011, mol_012 (Fe2+-promoted pyruvate-glyoxylate protometabolic network yielding oxaloacetate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_009: mol_005, mol_007 -> mol_009, mol_013, mol_014 (Metal-free pyruvate-glyoxylate mild aqueous network to alpha-ketoacid rTCA analogues including oxaloacetate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_010: mol_009, mol_007 -> mol_013 (HKG cycle entry: oxaloacetate plus glyoxylate to oxalomalate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_011: mol_013 -> mol_014 (HKG cycle decarboxylation: oxalomalate to 4-hydroxy-2-ketoglutarate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_012: mol_014, mol_015 -> mol_009, mol_010 (HKG cycle oxidation regenerating oxaloacetate and malate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_013: mol_009 -> mol_010 (ZnS photoreduction of oxaloacetate to malate in shallow photic mineral settings) [Surface]\n  - rxn_014: mol_010 -> mol_011 (Zn2+-promoted dehydration of malate to fumarate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_015: mol_011 -> mol_012 (ZnS photo